text=:Category: EndangeredLanguages%0a:Expansion: Revitalization Efforts of the Manchu Language and What It Means %0a:Author: yuluz%0a:Original: [[Articles.Manchu|Manchu]] %0a:OriginalAuthor: [[Profiles.lauray|lauray]]%0a:Section: C%0a:Completed: 08.05.2021 - 14:35%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeExpansion:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a%0a%25red%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210511-014351-311670#%0a* [-10.05.2021 - 18:43-] || TA_lili marked as complete%0a#foxend 210511-014351-311670#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25red%25 '''Comments to student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aToday, the Chinese government and some ethnic Manchurians are becoming more conscious about saving the Manchu Language. By simply googling about saving Manchu language online, we can find quite a few documentaries and news articles by the Chinese central media on the issue (links attached at the end). %0a%0aOne of the most widespread language revitalization effort is by Tan Shanshan, a cultural inheritor of the Manchu language. He opened both online and offline classes in China to help save the language. The hashtag for his online classes earned 160 million views on China's social media Weibo, with many Chinese netizens saying they support the conservation of China's ethnic minority languages. %0a%0aHowever, given the prevalence of Mandarin in China today, I think it is nearly impossible for people to begin use the Manchu language in daily interactions again even after they have learned it. I agree with many scholars that the importance of preserving this language lies more in its research value. Since the Manchu language was one of the official languages of the Manchu-led Qing Dynasty(1644-1911), many scripts and documents from that time period were written in this language. Thus, preserving the language is critical for the study of that 300 years of history in China. %0a%0aReports on revitalization efforts of the Manchu Language:%0a1. Plans to save ‘critically endangered’ Manchu language are spreading to preserve ethnic culture (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X1eeAGr-jzs)%0a2. Saving the Manchu Language (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nCFG-cbQOJc)%0a3. Cultural inheritor opens classes to save endangered Manchu language (https://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1172117.shtml)%0a%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:Category:)%0a(:GradedBy: TA_lili:)
